NCAA BASKETBALL - SMITH REACHES 11TH FINAL FOUR AS N . C . WHIPS LOUISVILLE . Dean Smith reached his 11th NCAA basketball tournament Final Four as coach of North Carolina on Sunday as the Tar Heels whipped sixth - seeded Louisville 97 - 74 in the East Region final . Shammond Williams scored 22 points and Vince Carter had five points in a key second - half run as North Carolina squandered most of a 21 - point halftime lead before running away for a 23 - point victory . North Carolina became the third top - seeded team to safely reach the Final Four in Indianapolis . Defending champions and West Region winner Kentucky and Midwest Region champion Minnesota nailed down final four spots Saturday . Fourth - seeded Arizona was leading 10th - seeded Providence 32 - 31 at halftime in the Southest region final at Birmingham , Alabama . Arizona stunned top - ranked , top - seeded Kansas in the Southeast regional semifinals . Carter finished with 15 points for the Tar Heels ( 28 - 6 ) , who had all five starters score in double figures and extended their winning streak to 16 games . Smith , who passed legendary Kentucky coach Adolph Rupp to move atop the all - time college basketball wins list in the second round , will be looking for his third National title in his fourth trip to the Final Four this decade . Alex Sanders scored 20 points and Alvin Sims added 14 for Louisville , which was in the regional finals for the first time since 1986 , the last time the Cardinals won the NCAA Tournament . Williams scored 15 of his points in the first half as North Carolina stormed out to a 54 - 33 halftime lead . The Cardinals , with starting point guard DeJuan Wheat playing on a badly sprained left ankle , made a run at the Tar Heels in the second half using bursts of 7 - 1 and 8 - 0 to pull within seven points at 59 - 52 with 13 : 29 left . B . J . Flynn hit two three - pointers to cap a 9 - 3 run for Louisville and with 8 : 14 to go the Cardinals were down by just one three - pointer at 69 - 66 . But the Cardinals went cold , missing on nine consecutive shots as North Carolina pulled away for the victory . " One thing about this team is there ' s no quit in them , " said longtime Louisville coach Denny Crum . " I think that second half run showed the kind of character that they have , and they ' ve done that all year . I know we kind of ran out of gas , but we made a great run at them . " 
